world survey of genomics research world survey of genomics research a project of the stanford in washington program funded by the burroughs wellcome fund in collaboration with the global forum for health research and the world health organization we are surveying funders of genomics research throughout the world the survey includes government programs nonprofit organizations pharmaceutical firms and dedicated genomics firms both publicly traded and privately held for information about the survey form and the organizations and individuals to be surveyed enter here robert cook deegan md amber lynn johnson research assistant carmie chan research assistant if you know of an organization that should be surveyed or if you have comments about the project please email me stanford seal
